{
  "text": "As to the imaging features of ES, Somarouthu, et al. reported the imaging features of twenty-six extraskeletal ESs [CITATION_1] . They found that the extra-skeletal ESs showed as an iso-density on CT, as a hypo-or isointensity on T1WI, and hyper-intensity on T2WI. Necrosis, hemorrhage and adjacent organ invasion could be par tially detected, while calcification was never seen.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "25428745"
